    "comment": "Rationale: In synaptosomal fractions from hippocampal CA1 tissues GluN2B protein levels were significantly increased in Eps8-/- mice.\n\n22/6/2017 Pim\nFig.3 \" Conditional deletion of Eps8 elevates synaptic GluN2B-containing NMDAR activity\"\nFig.4 \"Conditional deletion of Eps8 increases synaptic GluN2B subunit expression\"\nThese two lines of evidence show that the number of receptor molecules in the synaptic density are increased.\n- ifenprodil used as Glun2B-selective antagonist. Experimental description: \"synaptosomal fraction from hippocampal CA1 tissues to examine the expression patterns of NMDAR subunits in WT and Eps8-/- mice'\"",
